    • Method Detail

      • traverse

        void traverse(DirectoryTraversal traversal)
       throws IOException
        Takes a DirectoryTraversal and ensures that DirectoryTraversal.visit(java.nio.file.Path, String) is invoked, as appropriate. Normally, this is handled by invoking the traversal's DirectoryTraversal.traverse() method, though this extra level of abstraction makes it possible to inject different behavior for unit tests.
        Throws:
        IOException
